    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Limiting Cell Phones On the L.I.R.R.</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert Lewis letter on September 10 article holds cell phones should be banned or segregated on Long Island Rail Road (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Re the Sept. 10 article ''Cell Phone Abuse Is Riding the Rails:''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Re the Sept. 10 article ''Cell Phone Abuse Is Riding the Rails:''</p>
        <p>I employ my commuting time to read, which I cannot do when others are talking. Some officials and commuters suggested that education was the solution, but this would take a long, ongoing effort. Only a total ban or segregation to separate cars would be viable. It worked with smoking, why not phoning?</p>
        <p>ROBERT LEWIS  Great Neck</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
